The paper deals with algorithms for processing matrices in a stream, which is a common problem in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on low rank matrix approximations, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the limitations of adapting the algorithm to a sparse version, which is relevant to sparse data structures (cs.SI).
